  <h1><b><div style="color:#0000CE" id="createoredit">Mobi <span style="color:#ffab07">Sign-up</span><span id='stepcount' class='topspan' style='float:right;font-size:25px;margin-right:100px;'>Step 1 of 5</span></div></b></h1>

    <div class='page' id='page1'>
      <span style="color:black">Welcome to Mobi!</span> The following steps will ask you about where you are going and what you are looking for, so that your friends and the people we hire can best plan a custom-tailored itinerary for a day of your trip.
      <p>Your name: <input type="text" size="40" id="creator"></input></p>
      <p>Your email: <input type="text" size="40" id="creatoremail"></input></p>
      <p>What North American city are you visiting for which you'd like people to plan a day trip for you?<br/>(if the city you are visiting isn't listed, just let us know)<br/><input type="text" class="ui-autocomplete-input" name="city" size="40" id="city"></input></p>
      
      Please review the following information about what participation in this research study entails:<br/>
<!-- f2f2f2 -->

      <div style="background:white;border:solid 1px #DADADA;overflow-x:hidden;padding:15px;position:relative;height:280px;width:680px;font:14px/20px Georgia, Garamond, Serif;">
	<!-- <textarea rows="10" cols="80" readonly="readonly">-->
	<b>Purpose of the research:</b> To understand how you, your friends, and people we hire can use Mobi to plan itineraries for a day of a trip.
	<br/><br/>
	<b>What you will do in this research</b>: If you decide to participate, you will:
	<ul>
	  <li>Sign up by providing details on what you are looking for in this day trip. This is then given to your friends and people we hire, who will plan a day of your trip during the 
	    one-week period immediately after you sign up. You will be able to make edits as you see fit throughout the planning process.</li>
	  <li>Recruit your friends to help plan your trip for you using Mobi.</li>
	  <li>Keep track of how the plans are coming along over the course of the week (you will receive digest emails) and make suggestions or changes as you see fit.</li>
	  <li>Review the two final itineraries and complete a followup survey.</li>
	</ul>
	<b>Time required</b>: About 10-15 minutes to sign up and about 20-25 minutes for
	the post-survey. A few minutes a day to check on how the itineraries are coming along.
	<br/><br/>
	<b>Benefits</b>: You get two custom-tailored itineraries as well as a collection of activities of potential interest. You will also receive a <b>$30 Amazon gift card</b> upon completing the followup survey!
	<br/><br/>
	<b>Confidentiality</b>: Data collected will contain personal identifiers, but no personal information will be shared publicly nor published.
	<br/><br/>
	<b>Participation and withdrawal</b>: Your participation is completely voluntary, and you may quit at any time without penalty. You may skip any questions or tasks you do not want to answer or complete. In participating, you agree to not post anything illegal nor any personally identifiable information beyond what is requested.
	<br/><br/>
	<b>To Contact the Researcher</b>: If you have questions or concerns about this research, please contact:<br/>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Haoqi Zhang<br/>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Email: hq@eecs.harvard.edu<br/>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Phone: 9174452626<br/>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Address: 33 Oxford St. Room 219, Cambridge, MA 02138<br/><br/>
 You may also contact the faculty member supervising this work: David Parkes (parkes@eecs.harvard.edu), 33 Oxford St. Room 233, Cambridge, MA 02138<br/>
	<br/>
	<b>Whom to contact about your rights in this research, for questions, concerns, suggestions, or complaints that are not being addressed by the researcher, or research-related harm:</b>    Jane Calhoun, Harvard University Committee on the Use of Human Subjects in Research, 1414 Massachusetts Avenue, Second Floor, Cambridge, MA  02138.  Phone:  617-495-5459.  E-mail: jcalhoun@fas.harvard.edu
